710482f-b.text:
Tenth Avenue, west side, north from W. 18th Street (extreme left and not seen ), showing structures occupying the 19th-20th Street frontage. At the left is a vacant lot on the eaaterly half of the 18th-19th Street block and across which appears buildings on the north aide of W. 19th Street. The gap shown there was caused by the demolition in 19E0 of a 3 story tenement, No. 5O7-9 W. 19th Street. View No. 2 is a closer view of this N.W. corner of the Avenue and W. 19th Street and :hows in addition the renovation of the adjoininm
atructure to the aforerentioned gap.
